 Ref number
 Req_00053682
 Primary Location
 Home Office - United States
 Description and Requirements
 Main Responsibilities 
Operate video recording and lighting equipment. 
Organize, setup and prepare simple sets, props and wardrobes. 
Assist and coach talent before and during their performance. 
Manage filming schedules and other paperwork. 
Comply with safety and security requirements (e.g., set lock-down). 
Cooperate and report regularly to Director, Project Managers and other team members. 
Minimum Requirements 
Must be located within a reasonable commuting distance to San Jose, California. 
Full-time availability (up to 40 hours/week). 
Experience in the video production field, especially as an operator or Production Assistant. 
Experience in basic talent coaching. 
Excellent customer service attitude. 
Experience in working in a global environment. 
Very organized, self-driven and able to work independently. 
Outspoken, friendly and have positive attitude to different people. 
Experience with Google Workspace Apps ( Gmail, Drive, Docs, Sheets). 
Able to work in a highly secure and confidential environment. 
Ability to speak other languages is a plus. 
 Additional Job Description
